name: Tornado Watch
summary: Severe weather warnings have been issued across several regions, including the Southern Tier and WNY counties, West Michigan counties, the North Country and Vermont, and parts of Western New York. The National Weather Service has issued tornado watches, urging residents to seek shelter immediately. First Alert Weather Day has been declared in some areas, while university employees have been advised to evacuate by 3:30 p.m. due to the threat of tornadoes. The high-end Tornado Watch in Southwest Michigan warns of gusts up to 90 mph, while a Tornado Watch and Warning is in effect for all Western New York counties. Counties in Monroe, Ontario, and the surrounding areas are also under a tornado watch.
